Document Class

First test your LATEX has the beamer class installed

\documentclass[options]{beamer}
\mode&lt;presentation&gt;
{
\usetheme{Luebeck}
\usecolortheme{crane}
}

Fragile allows you to insert graphics into your powerpoint
envcountsect theorem environment counting is localized to section
compress makes navigation easier

Generating Title Page
\documentclass[11pt]{beamer}
\usepackage[utf8]{inputenc}
\usepackage[T1]{fontenc}
\usepackage{lmodern}
\usetheme{Madrid}
\begin{document}
    \author{Dr. Mutua}
    \title{Sample Presentation}
    \institute{Kirinyaga University}
    \date{July 2024}
    \begin{frame}[plain]
        \maketitle
    \end{frame}
\end{document}

Generating a New Slide

We use the following format

\section[short name]{full name}
\begin{frame}[options]
\frametitle{title of slide here}
\end{frame}

The options are:

shrink starts the first line at the top of the slide instead of starting in the middle
fragile allows you to do more sophisticated overlays
containsverbatim allows you to use verbatim environment

Generating an Outline
\begin{frame}
\frametitle{Outline}
\tableofcontents
\end{frame}

At the start of every slide have the following syntax

\section{Introduction}
\begin{frame}
    \frametitle{Introduction}

\end{frame}

Definitions in Slides

For definition use the following:

\begin{frame}
    \begin{definition}[Definition title]
        Here is definition.
    \end{definition}
\end{frame}

To number the definition or theorem use the following syntax in the preamble \setbeamertemplate{theorems}[numbered]

Example

You can define example using the following syntax

\begin{example}

\end{example}

Blocks

You can define blocks in beamer as:

\begin{block}{Snazzy Block Title}
You can ...
\end{block}

Use of Alert in Beamer

You can emphasize text like this in beamer:

\begin{alertblock}{Alert Block Title}
\end{alertblock}

Splitting a Slide into columns

One is able to split slides into two columns especially when explaining an output

\begin{columns}
\begin{column}{3cm}
\begin{block}{Smaller Column 1} ... \end{block}
\end{column}
\begin{column}{5cm}
\begin{block}{Bigger Column 2} ... \end{block}
\end{column}
\end{columns}

Lists in Beamer

Lists are done the same way we do while typsetting in Latex

\begin{enumerate}
\item
\end{enumerate}

% or

\begin{itemize}
\item 
\end{itemize}

Text Color

You can highlight a text in a different color using the following syntax \textcolor{blue}{Text you want}
Ensure you have loaded the package color or xcolor before execution.

References

We learnt how to use JabRef to do citations and the same way you do in document class article or report is the same you do citations here.
Use the following Synatx

\begin{frame}[allowframebreaks]{References}
\frametitle{Selected References}
\bibliographystyle{apalike}
\bibliography{phdref.bib}
\end{frame}

You can have a thank you slide for your audience as:

    \begin{frame}
    \begin{center}
    \LARGE \color{blue}\textbf{THANK YOU}
    \end{center}
    \end{frame}

