Inline Math Mode

You can use any of these delimiters to typeset your math in inline mode:

\(...\)
$...$
\begin{math}...\end{math}

They all work and the choice is a matter of taste.

\begin{document}
Equation \(E=mc^2\)

Instead use $E=mc^2$

Another option can be 

\begin{math}E=mc^2\end{math}
\end{document}

Display Math Mode

Use one of these constructions to typeset maths in display mode:

\[\]
\begin{displaymath}...\end{displaymath}
begin{equation}...\end{equation}

Cont’d

Display math mode has two versions which produce numbered or unnumbered equations.

# numbered equations
\begin{equation}\label{eqn1}
y = mx +c
\end{equation}

Equation \ref{eqn1} shows
\[\begin{equation}
\label{eqn1}
y = mx +c
\end{equation}\]
# unnumbered equations

\begin{equation*}
y = mx +c
\end{equation*}
\[\begin{equation*}
y = mx +c
\end{equation*}\]

Cont’d

